description:
File: lichen/subsys/lichen/transport/kiss_transport.c
Lines: 76-82

kiss_decode_init() checks for NULL ctx:

    void kiss_decode_init(struct kiss_decode_ctx *ctx)
    {
        if (ctx == NULL) {
            return;
        }
        memset(ctx, 0, sizeof(*ctx));
    }

This function is called from:
1. kiss_transport_init() line 498: kiss_decode_init(&ctx->rx_ctx) - ctx is &s_ctx, never NULL
2. kiss_rx_thread_fn() line 398: kiss_decode_init(&ctx->rx_ctx) - ctx is p1 argument, always valid
3. kiss_transport_test_inject_rx() line 676: kiss_decode_init(&ctx->rx_ctx) - ctx is &s_ctx
4. kiss_transport_test_reset() line 714: kiss_decode_init(&ctx->rx_ctx) - ctx is &s_ctx

In all cases, ctx points to a valid rx_ctx within the global s_ctx. The NULL check is dead code.

This is a minor issue but inconsistent with kiss_decode_byte() which does use its NULL check for early return with error code.

Fix: Remove the NULL check for consistency, or add a return value to indicate the check failed.
